8:
So... what "urgent quest" do you have 
for us?
10: You guys remember the Creole kid?
18: What's he up to this time?
21:
Why don't you go see for yourself? 
Be a lot faster than listening to my 
gums flap on.
26:
Okay... So tail the kid on his first errand, 
help out if anything goes wrong. 
Seems simple enough.
29:
Yes. He's going on a shopping trip. 
Hardly a dangerous task.
34: That's not what I was told!
46:
Come on, kid. All you have to do is carry 
one measly little box. Then you can buy 
all the manors you want!
51:
Look, the contract says I should be 
going shopping!
68:
It seems there was a misunderstanding. 
If the task is urgent, we can take it.
73:
But first, let's see what you're trying to 
ship!
89:
What'd I tell you?!
Swords out, boys! Beat 'em back!
100:
I will now proceed to chant a spell. 
Ahem!
103:
O, great voice that rattles the 
mountains and shakes the plains! 
Speak, and let the path before me be 
opened!
117:
You know some adventurers up in the 
desert... And you were trying to 
smuggle them an assorted selection of 
water monsters?
121:
Not everything is a box of chocolates, 
Alk.
124: Hey, don't treat us like common crooks!
125:
We're do-gooders, see? Trying to 
introduce folks to lifeforms they 
wouldn't otherwise meet, see?
126:
The crowds would've been thrilled, 
enthralled, and shocked right out of 
their socks!
133: The transport of monsters is perilous.
136:
We know, we know! Why do you think 
we got the world's best lightning mage 
on the job? Type advantage, and all 
that.
145:
Yeah. I've heard a lot of good stuff 
about you. 
They call you a child prodigy.
150: That is not a good enough reason to overlook your actions.
152:
You knew you were attempting 
something dangerous. 
Otherwise, you would not have lied to 
the Guild.
159:
The Guild cracks down on this kind of 
stuff, you know.
163:
I figured it out! We just have to flip 
everything!
170: So if transporting monsters is illegal...
172: Why don't we just bring the people to them?
179:
How the heck are we supposed to run 
a safari?
182:
Sell 1,000 gold tour packages that 
include transportation, housing, and 
security. 
The Guild will help provide these for 
a fee of, say, 400 gold. The difference is 
profit.
185:
So you're looking to form a partnership 
with the Guild.
188:
Yep. Plus, once the venture's in full 
swing and the orders are pouring in, 
we can haggle for a lower fee. 
The Guild keeps a steady source of 
income, and we strike it rich. 
See? Win-win.
192:
Very well thought out. I don't foresee the 
Guild raising any objections.
195:
Oh, and then there's souvenirs! 
We can team up with local merchants 
and set up a marketplace. 
A portion of all proceeds will go to us.
199:
Holy smokes! He really is a prodigy! 
A money-making genius!
205:
You like the idea? Then come on! 
Let's go pitch it to the Guild!
207:
No longer are we errand boys or 
smugglers! From today, we are 
visionaries! We are ENTREPRENEURS!
